description: Local elections were held across Russia on September 12 and 14. The campaign was particularly dull in Kostroma, a tourist town northeast of Moscow, revealing a society stifled by repression and overcome by apathy and weariness.

The Paris district where Parisians are priced out
description: In 50 years, the 8th arrondissement of the French capital, home to the Champs-Elysées and the 'Golden Triangle,' has lost nearly half its population. The mass acquisition of real estate by ultra-wealthy foreigners has driven locals out.

headline: Qatar owns 20% of property on Paris' Champs-Elysées
description: By reviewing land registry records, Le Monde determined that one-fifth of the facades on Paris's prestigious avenue are owned by the small Gulf monarchy.

headline: Summer 2025 heat waves cost France over €10 billion
description: Recent heat waves, droughts and floods are expected to slow economic activity in 2025 and beyond. The losses far exceed the damages reported by insurers.

Undercover but never unmasked: The untold story of a KGB spy in France
description: Following archival research and interviews with witnesses, Le Monde pieced together the completely unknown story of 'Lydia Tows,' a Russian agent who died in Paris in 1999. Working in tandem with a French police officer, she carried out a decades-long infiltration mission with devastating consequences.

headline: The thorny issue of splitting expenses in a relationship: 'Going 50/50 is a scam'
description: When moving in together, the question of 'who pays for what?' is often avoided. To break this taboo, social media content encourages couples to manage their finances more fairly, particularly to ensure that women are less disadvantaged.

headline: Is ChatGPT's fake empathy a threat to mental health?
description: Do conversational artificial intelligences pose a dangerous risk of emotional addiction for vulnerable individuals, or even the general public? Le Monde spoke with addiction specialists.
